rComments: His a really good professor, but the class is just not that interesting. He does his best to make it appealing for people, and he does a good job lecturing. You'll be marked on a few papers and they are quite essay to do. The feedback is helpful and if you go see him, he'll be happy and help you until you understand.
Talk too much about anything else, go too far...

Very boring lectures and confusing material. It seemed more like a philosophy than a political science class. If you study you will get good marks but you need to do research in order to understand the material because it wasn't clear in class.

This teacher is amazing, he knows his subject and his passionate by it. If you don't understand ask questions he loves it or go and see him in his office, if he see's you are trying your best he will help you a lot. Really friendly. I do recommend his class for sure.
Pierre Boyer was a great professor and the course was interesting. The only thing is he doesn't really give feedback on papers and his lectures are long.
He is a GREAT prof! Always there if you need help or clarification! I would recommend him to anyone!!
